<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In the bind() in the Zend_Ldap class the call</p>

<p>$username = $this-&gt;getCanonicalAccountName($username,
                        Zend_Ldap::ACCTNAME_FORM_PRINCIPAL);</p>

<p>is hard coded for UPN and ignores what is set in the options array.  We are unable to authenticate with MS Active Directory using this code.  If I change the Zend_Ldap::ACCTNAME_FORM_PRINCIPAL to $_options['accountCanonicalForm'] and set 3 in the config file all is well.  I'm not sure if the usage of  Zend_Ldap::ACCTNAME_FORM_PRINCIPAL is intentional.  I think the permitted options is setOptions should set a default value and then all calls to getCanonicalAccountName() can use what's in the $_options array.</p>

<p>I can patch and test the code and submit it that helps.</p>

